le ambiguity. Religion of nature, as it is laid out and explained here, confronts this problem and offers a comprehensive, sustaining, and fully adequate way of conceiving and living a religious life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aNaturalismxReligious aspects. 0aNaturexReligious aspects. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147793940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477939423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477939/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles